  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1672751884829-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1672751884829-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1672751884829-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1672751884829-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-2-1672751884829-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> in half lengthways and score the flesh quite deeply (in a diamond pattern) taking care not to cut through the skin</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine halves </strong>to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15-20 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672751887398-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672751887398-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672751887398-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672751887398-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1672751887398-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and<strong> agave </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>cornflour </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>and set aside until later – this is your <strong>sesame marinade</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a knob of <strong>butter alternative </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> and <strong>remaining tamari soy sauce</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672751890079-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672751890079-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672751890079-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672751890079-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1672751890079-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1672751892953-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1672751892953-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1672751892953-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1672751892953-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1672751892953-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is starting to soften, take the tray out of the oven and spread the<strong> sesame marinade </strong>over the aubergine</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a final 10-15 min or until tender – this is your <strong>oven-baked sticky sesame aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1672751895713-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1672751895713-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1672751895713-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1672751895713-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1672751895713-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1672751898189-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1672751898189-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1672751898189-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1672751898189-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1672751898189-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rinse your <strong>blanched edamame</strong> <strong>beans </strong>under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Once the rice is cooked, stir the <strong>spinach</strong> and <strong>blanched edamame beans </strong>through and cover until the spinach has wilted – this is your <strong>hoisin rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1672751902393-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1672751902393-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1672751902393-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1672751902393-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1672751902393-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, top the <strong>hoisin rice </strong>with the <strong>oven-baked sticky sesame aubergine</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> and drizzle over any<strong> remaining juices</strong> from the aubergine</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
      "order": 8,
